.TH MALDET "1" "March 2026" "Linux Malware Detect v2.0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
maldet \- Linux malware scanner for shared hosting environments
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B maldet
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B maldet
(Linux Malware Detect) is an open\-source malware scanner designed for
Linux shared hosting environments.
It provides multi\-stage detection using MD5 and SHA\-256 hashes, HEX patterns,
compound signatures (csig), statistical analysis, native YARA rules, and
optional ClamAV integration.
Detected threats can be quarantined, cleaned, or reported via email,
Slack, Telegram, and Discord.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Scanning
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-scan\-all\fR \fIPATH\fR
Scan all files in \fIPATH\fR (default: /home).
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-scan\-recent\fR \fIPATH\fR \fIDAYS\fR
Scan files created or modified in the last \fIDAYS\fR days (default: 7).
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\-list\fR \fIFILE\fR
Scan files listed in \fIFILE\fR, one path per line.
.TP
\fB\-b\fR, \fB\-\-background\fR
Run the scan operation in the background. May appear anywhere in the command line.
.SS Filters
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-include\-regex\fR \fIREGEX\fR
Include only paths matching POSIX extended regular expression.
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.TP
\fB\-x\fR, \fB\-\-exclude\-regex\fR \fIREGEX\fR
Exclude paths matching POSIX extended regular expression.
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.SS Monitoring
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-monitor\fR \fIUSERS\fR|\fIPATHS\fR|\fIFILE\fR|\fIRELOAD\fR
Start inotify real\-time monitoring.
By default, the supervisor runs in the foreground and holds the terminal.
Use \fB\-b\fR before \fB\-\-monitor\fR to daemonize: \fBmaldet \-b \-m users\fR.
\fBusers\fR monitors homedirs of UIDs above \fBinotify_minuid\fR.
\fBPATHS\fR accepts a comma\-separated list.
\fBFILE\fR reads paths from a file.
\fBreload\fR triggers a configuration reload.
.TP
\fB\-k\fR, \fB\-\-kill\-monitor\fR (also: \fB\-kill\fR)
Stop the inotify monitoring service.
Sends SIGTERM to the supervisor for a clean shutdown; escalates to SIGKILL
after a 10-second timeout if the process does not exit.
.SS Quarantine and Restore
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quarantine\fR \fISCANID\fR
Quarantine all hits from scan report \fISCANID\fR.
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-clean\fR \fISCANID\fR
Attempt to clean malware from files in scan report \fISCANID\fR.
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-restore\fR \fIFILE\fR|\fISCANID\fR
Restore a quarantined file or all files from \fISCANID\fR.
.TP
\fB\-qd\fR \fIPATH\fR
Override the quarantine directory for this run.
\fIPATH\fR must exist or the command exits with an error.
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.SS Reporting
.TP
\fB\-e\fR, \fB\-\-report\fR [\fISCANID\fR|\fBlist\fR|\fBlatest\fR|\fBhooks\fR|\fBactive\fR]
View a scan report.
Use \fBlatest\fR for the most recent scan, \fBlist\fR for all reports,
\fBhooks\fR for hook scan activity (see HOOK SCANNING),
\fBactive\fR for running scans (equivalent to \fB\-L\fR).
Combine with \fB\-\-format\fR and \fB\-\-mailto\fR for output control.
.TP
\fB\-\-all\fR
Show full scan history when used with \fB\-e list\fR.
Without \fB\-\-all\fR, \fB\-e list\fR shows only recent sessions.
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.TP
\fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show additional detail with \fB\-L\fR (workers, signature version, progress).
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fBtext\fR|\fBjson\fR|\fBhtml\fR|\fBtsv\fR
Set report output format for \fB\-e\fR/\fB\-\-report\fR and \fB\-L\fR (default: text).
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.TP
\fB\-\-mailto\fR \fIADDRESS\fR
Email the report to the specified address instead of stdout.
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.TP
\fB\-\-json\-report\fR [\fISCANID\fR|\fBlist\fR]
Shorthand for \fB\-\-report \-\-format json\fR.
Output a JSON\-formatted scan report for the given \fISCANID\fR.
Use \fBlist\fR to output all scan reports as a JSON array.
Supports both TSV and legacy plaintext sessions.
.TP
\fB\-\-alert\-daily\fR (also: \fB\-\-monitor\-report\fR)
Generate a digest alert summarizing inotify monitor activity.
Requires monitor mode to be running.
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-log\fR
Display the event log.
.SS Updates
.TP
\fB\-u\fR, \fB\-\-update\-sigs\fR (also: \fB\-\-update\fR) [\fB\-\-force\fR]
Update malware signatures from rfxn.com.
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-update\-ver\fR (also: \fB\-\-update\-version\fR) [\fB\-\-force\fR|\fB\-\-beta\fR]
Update the LMD installation to the latest version.
.TP
\fB\-\-cron\-sigup\fR
Perform a signature update for the independent cron job.
Serialized with \fBflock\fR to prevent concurrent runs.
Includes a random 0\-120s sleep to avoid upstream stampede.
Internal use only \(em invoked by
.IR /etc/cron.d/maldet\-sigup ;
not intended for direct invocation.
.SS Other
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-checkout\fR \fIFILE\fR
Upload a suspected malware sample to rfxn.com for analysis.
.TP
\fB\-\-mkpubpaths\fR
Create per\-user pub/ data directories for non\-root scan operations.
Requires \fBscan_user_access=1\fR in conf.maldet.
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-purge\fR
Clear logs, quarantine queue, session, and temporary data.
.TP
\fB\-U\fR, \fB\-\-user\fR \fIUSER\fR
Run as the specified user (for viewing reports or restoring quarantine).
.TP
\fB\-co\fR, \fB\-\-config\-option\fR \fIVAR\fR=\fIVAL\fR[,\fIVAR\fR=\fIVAL\fR,...]
Override configuration options at runtime.
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.TP
\fB\-\-web\-proxy\fR (also: \fB\-\-wget\-proxy\fR, \fB\-\-curl\-proxy\fR) \fIIP\fR:\fIPORT\fR
Set HTTP/HTTPS proxy for all remote connections.
.TP
\fB\-hscan\fR, \fB\-\-hook\-scan\fR (also: \fB\-\-modsec\fR)
Scan a single file supplied by a service hook (ModSecurity, pure\-ftpd,
ProFTPD, Exim, or custom).
Used internally by \fBhookscan.sh\fR; not intended for direct invocation.
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.TP
\fB\-\-digest\fR
Fire a unified digest alert reading all available sources: monitor session
hits, hook scan hits, cleaned/suspended history.
Does not require monitor mode \(em fires if any source has new data since
the last digest.
Cursors advance on read, preventing duplicate alerts.
.TP
\fB\-\-test\-alert\fR \fITYPE\fR \fICHANNEL\fR
Send a test alert with synthetic data to verify alerting configuration.
\fITYPE\fR: \fBscan\fR (per\-scan alert with 3 synthetic hits) or
\fBdigest\fR (periodic summary).
\fICHANNEL\fR: \fBemail\fR, \fBslack\fR, \fBtelegram\fR, or \fBdiscord\fR.
Uses the real rendering pipeline with a \fB[TEST]\fR subject prefix.
Channel isolation ensures only the specified channel receives the alert.
Requires root privileges.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Display version information.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Display usage information.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success; no malware found.
.TP
.B 1
Error or invalid arguments; or all provided scan paths do not exist.
.TP
.B 2
Malware hits detected.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/conf.maldet
User configuration file.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/internals.conf
Internal paths, binary discovery, and URL definitions.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/compat.conf
Backward compatibility variable mappings.
.TP
.B /usr/local/maldetect/internals/lmd.lib.sh
Core library sourcing hub \(em sources all sub-libraries in dependency order.
.TP
.B /usr/local/maldetect/internals/lmd_*.sh
Decomposed function libraries: lmd_config, lmd_init, lmd_clamav, lmd_sigs,
lmd_engine, lmd_yara, lmd_quarantine, lmd_session, lmd_scan, lmd_monitor,
lmd_update, lmd_alert.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/alert_lib.sh
Shared alerting library (email, Slack, Telegram, Discord delivery).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/lmd_alert.sh
LMD-specific alert functions (data preparation, rendering pipeline).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/alert/
Alert template directory (HTML, text, and messaging templates).
Custom overrides go in
.I alert/custom.d/
and are preserved across upgrades.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/tlog_lib.sh
Shared incremental log reading library.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/elog_lib.sh
Shared structured event logging library.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/pkg_lib.sh
Shared packaging utility library (RPM/DEB manifest helpers).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sigs/
Signature directory (MD5, SHA\-256, HEX, CSIG, YARA, ClamAV).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sigs/csig.dat
Compound signature rules (multi\-pattern boolean logic).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sigs/custom.csig.dat
User\-defined compound signature rules.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sigs/sha256v2.dat
SHA\-256 hash signatures (HASH:SIZE:{SHA256}sig.name.N).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sigs/custom.sha256.dat
User\-defined SHA\-256 hash signatures.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sigs/rfxn.hsb
ClamAV SHA\-256 hash signature database (ClamAV >= 0.97).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/conf.maldet.hookscan
Hook scan configuration (user\-customizable, preserved across upgrades).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/conf.maldet.hookscan.default
Reference hook scan configuration with default values and documentation.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sess/hook.hits.log
Rolling hook scan detection log (TSV format, append\-only).
Each line is an 11\-field hit record plus hook mode and timestamp.
Read by digest alerts and
.BR "\-\-report hooks" .
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/quarantine/
Quarantine storage for detected malware.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sess/session.tsv.*
TSV\-format scan session data files containing a 19\-field metadata header
and 11\-field hit records.
Canonical format as of v2.0.1.
.TP
.I /var/log/maldet/
Log directory (FHS). Contains
.IR event_log ,
.IR clamscan_log ,
.IR inotify_log ,
and
.IR audit.log .
.I /usr/local/maldetect/logs
is a backward\-compatible symlink to this directory.
.TP
.I /etc/logrotate.d/maldet
Logrotate configuration for event_log, clamscan_log, and audit.log.
Installed only when
.BR logrotate (8)
is available. Does not rotate inotify_log (managed internally by
.BR \-\-maintenance ).
.TP
.I /etc/cron.daily/maldet
Daily cron job for automated scanning and updates.
.TP
.I /etc/cron.weekly/maldet\-watchdog
Weekly watchdog for fallback signature updates.
.TP
.I /etc/cron.d/maldet\-sigup
Independent signature update cron job (interval set by \fBsigup_interval\fR).
.TP
.I /etc/sysconfig/maldet " or " /etc/default/maldet
System\-level configuration overrides.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/monitor_paths.extra
Line-separated file of additional paths to add to the inotify watch list.
Managed independently of
.BR conf.maldet .
See
.B monitor_paths_extra
in the CONFIGURATION section.
.TP
.I $sessdir/scan.meta.$scanid
Scan lifecycle metadata. Contains process info, state, engine type,
scan options, and timestamps. Updated throughout the scan lifecycle
as state transitions occur.
.TP
.I $sessdir/session.index
Append\-only session index for O(1) scan listing. Each line records
the scan ID, start time, path, and completion status. Used by
\fB\-\-report list\fR and \fB\-L\fR for fast enumeration without
scanning the session directory.
.TP
.I $sessdir/scan.checkpoint.$scanid
Stage checkpoint file for \fB\-\-continue\fR. Written by \fB\-\-stop\fR
with the \fB#LMD_CHECKPOINT:v1\fR format. Contains the last completed
stage, accumulated hits, config options, and signature version at the
time of stop.
.TP
.I $tmpdir/.abort.$scanid
Abort sentinel. Created by \fB\-\-kill\fR or \fB\-\-stop\fR. Workers
check for this file at stage boundaries and during scan loops for
cooperative shutdown.
.TP
.I $tmpdir/.pause.$scanid
Pause sentinel with epoch timestamp and optional duration. Created by
\fB\-\-pause\fR. Workers enter a sleep loop while this file exists.
Removed by \fB\-\-unpause\fR or when the duration expires.
.TP
.I $sessdir/session.archive.YYMM.tsv.gz
Monthly session archive created by \fB\-\-maintenance\fR. Consolidates
all session TSV files from the given month (YYMM) into a single
gzip\-compressed archive. The \fB\-\-report\fR command transparently
resolves sessions from archives when the original session file has
been archived.
