.BR scan_days ,
.BR import_config_url ,
.BR import_config_expire ,
.BR session_legacy_compat .
.PP
.B Signature Import:
.BR sig_import_md5_url ,
.BR sig_import_hex_url ,
.BR sig_import_yara_url ,
.BR sig_import_sha256_url ,
.BR sig_import_csig_url .
.PP
.B autoupdate_version_hashed
validates the SHA\-256 hash of installed LMD executables against known good
upstream values on each update check.
Falls back to MD5 verification if sha256sum is unavailable.
Forces reinstallation on mismatch.
Default: 1.
.PP
.B sigup_interval
sets the interval in hours for automatic signature update checks via
the independent cron job
.RI ( /etc/cron.d/maldet\-sigup ).
This runs separately from
.I cron.daily
and is idempotent with
.BR "maldet \-u" .
Set to 0 to disable the independent cron job.
Valid range: 1\-24.
Default: 6.
.PP
.B scan_hashtype
selects the hash algorithm for file\-hash signature matching (stage 1).
Values: \fBauto\fR (use SHA\-256 if CPU has hardware acceleration, else MD5),
\fBsha256\fR (always SHA\-256),
\fBmd5\fR (always MD5; preserves performance on older CPUs without SHA\-NI),
\fBboth\fR (run both MD5 and SHA\-256 stages for maximum coverage).
Default: auto.
.PP
.B scan_clamscan
enables ClamAV as the scan engine for improved performance on large file sets.
When set to
.B auto
(default), LMD detects the clamscan binary at runtime and enables ClamAV
scanning only if available.
Values: \fBauto\fR (detect binary), \fB0\fR (disabled), \fB1\fR (enabled).
Default: auto.
.PP
.B scan_yara
enables native YARA scanning via the yara binary (or yr from YARA\-X).
When set to
.B auto
(default), LMD enables native YARA scanning only when ClamAV is unavailable
and a yara/yr binary is found.
This prevents duplicate YARA rule evaluation since ClamAV already processes
YARA rules internally.
To force native YARA alongside ClamAV, set to \fB1\fR and use
\fBscan_yara_scope\fR to control which rules each engine handles.
Values: \fBauto\fR (detect binary, ClamAV fallback), \fB0\fR (disabled),
\fB1\fR (enabled).
Default: auto.
.PP
.B scan_csig
enables compound signature (csig) scanning.
Compound signatures support multi\-pattern boolean logic (AND/OR/threshold),
case\-insensitive matching, wide (UTF\-16LE) matching, and bounded gap wildcards.
Runs in native mode only (not with ClamAV).
Default: 1.
.PP
.B scan_workers
sets the number of parallel workers for native MD5, SHA\-256, HEX, and CSIG scan passes.
A value of \fBauto\fR (default) uses automatic detection: 2 workers per CPU core, up to 8.
Set to 1 for single\-threaded operation.
Maximum value: 8.
.PP
.B scan_find_timeout
sets the maximum execution time in seconds for the
.BR find (1)
file list generation phase.
A value of 0 disables the timeout.
Values between 1 and 59 are silently ignored (minimum is 60).
Default: 0.
.PP
.B scan_progress_log_interval
sets the interval in seconds between progress checkpoints written to the
event log during background scans
.RB ( "maldet \-b" ).
Each checkpoint reports the current scan stage, files processed, percentage
complete, elapsed time, and estimated time remaining.
A value of 0 disables progress logging.
Default: 60.
.PP
.B scan_hexdepth
sets the maximum byte depth that the scanner reads from each file during
HEX signature matching (stage 2).
The default (262144 = 256\ KB) covers 98.9% of HEX patterns; the remaining
1.1% of deep patterns (php.inject.* at offsets > 256\ KB) are caught by
YARA stage 3 when
.B scan_yara
is enabled (default).
Higher values increase temporary disk usage during large scans.
Default: 262144.
.PP
.B scan_hex_chunk_size
sets the maximum number of files processed per micro\-batch during
HEX+CSIG scanning.
Lower values reduce temporary disk usage; higher values may improve throughput
on fast storage.
Valid range: 1024\(en20480.
Values outside this range are clamped with a logged warning.
To increase throughput, raise
.B scan_workers
instead.
To reduce disk usage, lower
.B scan_hexdepth
instead.
Default: 10240.
.PP
.B scan_days
sets the number of days to look back for recently modified files during
daily cron scans.
This value is passed as the \fIDAYS\fR argument to
.BR "maldet \-r" .
Default: 1.
.PP
.B email_format
sets the format for email alerts.
Values: \fBtext\fR (plain text only), \fBhtml\fR (HTML with text fallback),
\fBboth\fR (multipart alternative with both formats).
Default: html.
.PP
.B smtp_relay
sets an SMTP relay for email delivery instead of the local MTA.
When set, emails are sent via this relay using curl.
Examples: \fBsmtps://smtp.gmail.com:465\fR, \fBsmtp://relay.example.com:587\fR.
Requires \fBsmtp_from\fR to be set.
.PP
.B smtp_from
sets the sender address for SMTP relay delivery.
Required when \fBsmtp_relay\fR is set.
.PP
.B smtp_user
and
.B smtp_pass
set SMTP authentication credentials for relay delivery.
.PP
.B session_legacy_compat
controls generation of legacy plaintext session files alongside TSV.
Values: \fBauto\fR (detect old\-format sessions, enable if found \(em default),
\fB1\fR (always generate plaintext),
\fB0\fR (TSV only).
Default: auto.
.PP
.B ClamAV Signature Validation
.PP
When ClamAV is installed, LMD validates signature files via
.B clamscan \-d
against a staging directory before deploying them to ClamAV data
directories.
If validation fails, existing LMD signatures are removed from the
ClamAV path to protect ClamAV from loading malformed databases.
The
.B SIGUSR2
reload signal to
.B clamd
is only sent when at least one ClamAV data directory passes validation.
This prevents malformed signature updates from breaking ClamAV (issue #467).
.PP
.B digest_interval
sets the period between automatic digest summary alerts in monitor mode.
Accepts a numeric value with a unit suffix:
.B Nh
(hours),
.B Nm
(minutes),
.B Nd
(days).
Set to
.B 0
to disable periodic digests.
Default: 24h.
.PP
.B digest_escalate_hits
sets a hit-count threshold for immediate escalation alerts in monitor mode.
When the number of new hits detected since the last digest exceeds this value,
an alert is sent immediately rather than waiting for the next digest interval.
Set to
.B 0
to disable escalation.
Default: 0.
.PP
.B monitor_paths_extra
is the path to a line-separated file of additional paths to add to the
inotify watch list.
Entries in this file are merged with the primary watch list on every
configuration reload, allowing paths to be added without modifying
.B conf.maldet
or restarting the monitor.
Default: /usr/local/maldetect/monitor_paths.extra.
.PP
.B cron_digest_hook
enables the daily cron job hook digest sweep.
When enabled, cron.daily checks for new hook scan detections and fires a
digest alert if any exist since the last sweep.
Set to 0 to disable (e.g., if monitor mode handles hook digests).
Default: 1.
.PP
.B hookscan_timeout
sets the scan timeout in seconds for hook\-triggered scans.
ModSecurity has no built\-in timeout \(em this prevents Apache worker thread
exhaustion.
pure\-ftpd runs hook scripts sequentially \(em this prevents queue blocking.
Default: 30.
.PP
.B hookscan_fail_open
controls behavior when the scan subprocess exits with an unexpected error.
When set to 1 (default), scanner errors allow the file through (fail\-open).
When set to 0, scanner errors block the file (fail\-closed).
Fail\-open is the safe default: a broken scanner should not cause a
site\-wide upload outage.
Default: 1.
.PP
.B hookscan_escalate_hits
sets a hit\-count threshold for immediate hook scan escalation alerts.
When the number of hook detections within a 1\-hour rolling window reaches
this value, an immediate per\-scan alert is fired.
Set to 0 to disable escalation.
Default: 0.
.PP
.B hookscan_service_users
is a comma\-separated list of service account usernames exempt from the
non\-root homedir restriction.
Default: apache,nginx,www\-data,nobody,proftpd,exim.
.PP
.B hookscan_user_rate_limit
sets the maximum scans per hour for non\-root callers.
Hook\-triggered scans (ModSecurity, FTP) from service UIDs are exempt.
Set to 0 for unlimited.
Default: 60.
.PP
.B hookscan_user_show_signames
controls signature name visibility for non\-root callers.
When set to 0, non\-root users see opaque \(lqMALWARE\-DETECTED\(rq in output
while full signature names are logged.
When set to 1 (default), full signature names appear in all output.
Default: 1.
.PP
.B hookscan_list_max_bytes
sets the maximum file list size in bytes for batch scanning via
.BR "\-\-list" .
Default: 1048576 (1 MB).
.PP
.B hookscan_list_max_entries
sets the maximum number of entries accepted from a file list or stdin pipe.
Default: 10000.
.PP
.B Post\-Scan Hooks:
.BR post_scan_hook ,
.BR post_scan_hook_format ,
.BR post_scan_hook_exec ,
.BR post_scan_hook_timeout ,
.BR post_scan_hook_on ,
.BR post_scan_hook_min_hits .
.PP
.B post_scan_hook
is the path to an executable script invoked after scan completion.
The hook receives scan results via positional arguments
(\fI$1\fR=SCANID, \fI$2\fR=HITS, \fI$3\fR=FILES, \fI$4\fR=EXIT_CODE,
\fI$5\fR=SCAN_TYPE, \fI$6\fR=PATH) and \fBLMD_*\fR environment variables.
The script must be owned by root and not world\-writable.
Leave empty to disable.
This variable cannot be overridden via \fB\-co\fR for security.
Default: "" (disabled).
.PP
.B post_scan_hook_format
controls the output tier (each tier includes all previous tiers):
\fBargs\fR (positional args + env only),
\fBfile\fR (adds LMD_SESSION_FILE), or \fBjson\fR (adds JSON blob on stdin).
Default: args.
.PP
.B post_scan_hook_exec
controls execution mode: \fBasync\fR (fork, non\-blocking) or
\fBsync\fR (wait for completion).
Monitor mode always forces async regardless of this setting.
Default: async.
.PP
.B post_scan_hook_timeout
sets the timeout in seconds before SIGTERM, followed by SIGKILL after
a 5\-second grace period.
Set to 0 to disable.
Values 1\-4 are clamped to 5.
Default: 60.
.PP
.B post_scan_hook_on
filters which scan types trigger the hook: \fBall\fR, \fBcli\fR, or
\fBdigest\fR.
Default: all.
.PP
.B post_scan_hook_min_hits
sets the minimum malware hit count to trigger the hook.
Set to 0 to fire on every scan including clean ones.
Default: 1.
.PP
.B Scan Lifecycle:
.BR scan_progress_log_interval ,
.BR scan_meta_cleanup_age ,
.BR maint_compress_age ,
.BR maint_archive_age .
.PP
.B scan_meta_cleanup_age
sets the number of hours to retain completed/killed/stale scan.meta files
before cleanup.
Meta files for active/paused/stopped scans are never cleaned.
Set 0 to disable automatic cleanup. Default: 48.
.PP
.B maint_compress_age
sets the number of days before completed session files are compressed (gzipped).
Sessions younger than this age are never compressed.
Set 0 to disable automatic compression. Default: 30.
.PP
.B maint_archive_age
sets the number of days before compressed session files are bundled into
monthly archives.
Sessions younger than this age are never archived.
Set 0 to disable automatic archival. Default: 90.
.PP
See
.I conf.maldet
for the full list with descriptions.
.SH MONITOR MODE
The monitor command runs a supervisor process that manages an
.BR inotifywait (1)
child watching for file create, modify, and move events.
.PP
By default,
.B maldet \-m users
runs in the foreground, keeping the terminal occupied.
Use
.B maldet \-b \-m users
to daemonize the supervisor and return immediately.
The
.B \-b
flag may appear anywhere on the command line.
.PP
The supervisor automatically recovers from
.B inotifywait
crashes using exponential backoff (2, 4, 8, 16, 32 seconds).
After three consecutive failures the supervisor exits with a logged error.
.PP
.B maldet \-k
sends SIGTERM to the running supervisor for a clean shutdown.
If the process does not exit within 10 seconds, SIGKILL is sent.
.PP
A periodic digest summary alert is sent every
.B digest_interval
(default: 24h).
If the number of new hits since the last digest exceeds
.B digest_escalate_hits
(default: 0, disabled), an immediate escalation alert is sent regardless of the interval.
.PP
Additional watch paths can be supplied without modifying
.B conf.maldet
by listing them (one per line) in the file pointed to by
.BR monitor_paths_extra .
These are merged with the primary path list on every cycle reload.
.PP
.B Behavioral change \(em ignore_inotify entries are now treated as literal paths.
ERE metacharacters
.RI ( . ,
.IR * ,
.IR + ,
etc.) are automatically escaped before the path is used as a pattern.
Users who previously relied on ERE regex patterns in
.B ignore_inotify
should update their entries to use literal path strings.
.SH HOOK SCANNING
.B hookscan.sh
provides real\-time file scanning for service integrations.
It supports multiple output modes for different services:
.PP
.B hookscan.sh
[\fImode\fR] \fIfile\fR
.PP
Modes:
.TP
.B modsec
ModSecurity \fB@inspectFile\fR (default if no mode specified).
Stdout: \fB1\fR clean, \fB0 maldet: SIGNAME PATH\fR infected.
.TP
.B ftp
pure\-ftpd \fBpure\-uploadscript\fR daemon.
Fire\-and\-forget: quarantines on detect, no stdout needed.
Auto\-detected when the \fBUPLOAD_VUSER\fR environment variable is set.
.TP
.B proftpd
ProFTPD \fBmod_exec\fR.
Fire\-and\-forget: quarantines on detect, no stdout needed.
.TP
.B exim
Exim \fBcmdline\fR av_scanner.
Stdout: \fBmaldet: clean\fR or \fBmaldet: SIGNAME\fR.
.TP
.B generic
Machine\-parseable output for custom integrations.
Exit codes: 0 clean, 1 error, 2 infected.
Stdout: \fBCLEAN: PATH\fR, \fBINFECTED: SIGNAME PATH\fR, or
\fBERROR: reason\fR.
Accepts \fB\-\-list FILE\fR or \fB\-\-stdin\fR for batch file scanning.
.PP
Hook scan detections are logged to a rolling hit log
.RI ( hook.hits.log )
and included in periodic digest alerts.
Individual hook scans do not create session files or fire per\-scan alerts.
.PP
When the escalation threshold
.B hookscan_escalate_hits
is exceeded (N detections within a 1\-hour window), an immediate per\-scan
alert is fired regardless of digest settings.
.PP
Configuration options for hook scanning are stored in
.BR conf.maldet.hookscan .
The reference defaults are in
.BR conf.maldet.hookscan.default .
.PP
.B Backward compatibility:
.B hookscan.sh /path/to/file
(no mode argument) behaves identically to prior versions \(em ModSecurity mode.
.SS Batch File Lists (generic mode)
.TP
\fBhookscan.sh generic \-\-list\fR \fIFILE\fR
Scan files listed in \fIFILE\fR (one absolute path per line).
Each line is validated: absolute path required, no shell metacharacters,
no path traversal, no non\-printable characters.
Invalid lines are skipped with a syslog warning.
.TP
\fBhookscan.sh generic \-\-stdin\fR
Read file paths from stdin (pipe).
Same per\-line validation as \fB\-\-list\fR.
Terminal input is rejected.
.PP
Batch output produces one \fBSTATUS: PATH\fR line per file.
Exit code is worst\-result\-wins: 2 if any infected, 1 if any errors, 0 if
all clean.
.SS Usermode Restrictions
Non\-root callers are restricted to scanning files within their home directory.
Service UIDs listed in
.B hookscan_service_users
are exempt from this restriction.
Non\-root callers are subject to rate limiting via
.BR hookscan_user_rate_limit .
.SH TEST ALERTS
.B maldet \-\-test\-alert
\fITYPE\fR \fICHANNEL\fR
sends a synthetic test alert through the full rendering pipeline to verify
that a delivery channel is correctly configured.
.PP
.B TYPE
selects the alert template:
.TP
.B scan
Per\-scan alert with 3 synthetic hits (MD5, HEX, and YARA detection types).
Exercises the hit\-type color registry and per\-type template rendering.
.TP
.B digest
Periodic summary alert with synthetic data spanning all 5 digest sources.
.PP
.B CHANNEL
selects the delivery target:
.B email\fR,
.B slack\fR,
.B telegram\fR, or
.BR discord .
.PP
Channel isolation ensures only the specified channel receives the test alert;
all other channels are temporarily suppressed.
If the target channel is not enabled in
.IR conf.maldet ,
an error is reported.
.PP
The subject line is prefixed with
.B [TEST]
to distinguish test alerts from real detections.
.PP
Requires root privileges.
.PP
Examples:
.TP
Verify email alerting:
.B maldet \-\-test\-alert scan email
.TP
Verify Slack digest delivery:
.B maldet \-\-test\-alert digest slack
.SH DIGEST ALERTS
Digest alerts provide periodic summaries of detection activity from all
sources: inotify monitor hits, hook scan detections, cleaned files, and
suspended users.
.PP
Three trigger paths fire digest alerts:
.TP
.B Monitor timer
When monitor mode is running, a digest fires every
.B digest_interval
(default: 24h).
.TP
.B cron.daily
When
.B cron_digest_hook=1
(default), the daily cron job fires a digest if new hook scan detections
exist since the last sweep.
.TP
.B \-\-digest CLI
.B maldet \-\-digest
fires an on\-demand digest reading all 5 tlog\-cursored sources.
Cursors advance on read, so subsequent digests see only new data.
.PP
When monitor mode is not running, digest alerts can still fire via
cron.daily or \fB\-\-digest\fR if hook scan detections exist.
The monitor\-specific sections of the digest template render as empty
when monitor mode is inactive.
.SS Hook Scan Reports
.TP
\fBmaldet \-\-report hooks\fR
Display all hook scan detections from the rolling hit log (default: last 24h).
.TP
\fBmaldet \-\-report hooks \-\-last\fR \fIDURATION\fR
Filter by time: \fBNh\fR (hours), \fBNd\fR (days), \fBNm\fR (minutes).
.TP
\fBmaldet \-\-report hooks \-\-mode\fR \fIMODE\fR
Filter by hook mode: \fBmodsec\fR, \fBftp\fR, \fBproftpd\fR, \fBexim\fR,
or \fBgeneric\fR.
.SH SCAN MANAGEMENT
Scan lifecycle commands allow controlling running scans without terminating
the maldet process. Scans transition through a state machine:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
running \(-> paused   (\-\-pause)   \(-> running (\-\-unpause)
running \(-> killed   (\-\-kill)
running \(-> stopped  (\-\-stop)    \(-> running (\-\-continue)
running \(-> completed (normal exit)
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ClamAV limitation:
Daemon ClamAV (clamdscan) scans can only be killed (\fB\-\-kill\fR),
not paused or stopped.
Standalone clamscan and yara/yr processes support full lifecycle control
via SIGSTOP/SIGCONT.
.HP
\fB\-L\fR, \fB\-\-list\-active\fR
.IP
List active (running, paused, stale) scans with status information.
Combine with \fB\-\-format\fR for JSON or TSV output. Use \fB\-\-verbose\fR
for additional detail (workers, sig version, progress).
.br
e.g: maldet \fB\-L\fR
.br
e.g: maldet \fB\-\-format\fR json \fB\-L\fR
.HP
\fB\-\-report\fR active
.IP
View active scans. Equivalent to \fB\-L\fR but supports
\fB\-\-format\fR json|tsv output and integration with the report system.
.HP
\fB\-\-kill\fR \fISCANID\fR
.IP
Abort a running or paused scan. Writes an abort sentinel for cooperative
shutdown, then sends SIGTERM to the scan process (with SIGKILL fallback
after 30 seconds). Cleans scan\-scoped temporary files and updates meta
to state=killed. Also handles stale scans where the process has already
exited.
.br
e.g: maldet \fB\-\-kill\fR 260327\-1509.25279
.HP
\fB\-\-pause\fR \fISCANID\fR [\fIDURATION\fR]
.IP
Pause a running scan. Workers enter a sleep loop and external processes
(clamscan, yara) receive SIGSTOP. Optional \fIDURATION\fR auto\-resumes
after the specified time: \fIN\fRs (seconds), \fIN\fRm (minutes),
\fIN\fRh (hours), or a bare number (seconds). Without \fIDURATION\fR,
the pause is indefinite until \fB\-\-unpause\fR. Not supported for daemon
ClamAV (clamdscan) scans.
.br
e.g: maldet \fB\-\-pause\fR 260327\-1509.25279
.br
e.g: maldet \fB\-\-pause\fR 260327\-1509.25279 30m
.br
e.g: maldet \fB\-\-pause\fR 260327\-1509.25279 2h
.HP
\fB\-\-unpause\fR \fISCANID\fR
.IP
Resume a paused scan. Removes the pause sentinel and sends SIGCONT to
any stopped external processes.
.br
e.g: maldet \fB\-\-unpause\fR 260327\-1509.25279
.HP
\fB\-\-stop\fR \fISCANID\fR
.IP
Checkpoint and stop a running or paused scan at the current stage
boundary. Writes a checkpoint file (format \fB#LMD_CHECKPOINT:v1\fR)
preserving the scan state (stage, hits, options, signature version)
for later resumption via \fB\-\-continue\fR. Not supported for daemon
ClamAV (clamdscan) scans.
.br
e.g: maldet \fB\-\-stop\fR 260327\-1509.25279
.HP
\fB\-\-continue\fR \fISCANID\fR
.IP
Resume a previously stopped scan from its checkpoint. Compares the
current signature version with the checkpoint and warns if signatures
have changed since the scan was stopped. Restores \fB\-co\fR options from
the checkpoint. Use \fB\-\-unpause\fR for paused scans instead.
.br
e.g: maldet \fB\-\-continue\fR 260327\-1509.25279
.HP
\fB\-\-maintenance\fR
.IP
Run maintenance tasks: rotate oversized history files (hits.hist,
quarantine.hist, monitor.scanned.hist, inotify_log), clean up stale
scan meta files older than \fBscan_meta_cleanup_age\fR hours, compress
completed session files older than \fBmaint_compress_age\fR days, and
archive sessions older than \fBmaint_archive_age\fR days into monthly
bundles (\fIsession.archive.YYMM.tsv.gz\fR).
Intended for cron or manual housekeeping.
.br
e.g: maldet \fB\-\-maintenance\fR
.SS Checkpoint Format
The checkpoint file uses a simple key=value format with a
\fB#LMD_CHECKPOINT:v1\fR header line. Fields include:
\fBscanid\fR, \fBstopped\fR (epoch), \fBstage\fR (last completed stage),
\fBsig_version\fR, \fBworkers\fR, \fBtotal_files\fR, \fBhits_so_far\fR,
and \fBoptions\fR (original \fB\-co\fR values). The session hits file is
preserved across stop/continue so that accumulated detections are retained.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Scan all files under user web roots:
.B maldet \-a /home/?/public_html
.TP
Scan recent files with auto\-quarantine and YARA:
.B maldet \-co quarantine_hits=1,scan_yara=1 \-r /home/?/public_html 2
.TP
View the most recent scan report:
.B maldet \-e
.TP
List all scan reports:
.B maldet \-e list
.TP
Output a scan report as JSON:
.B maldet \-\-json\-report SCANID
.TP
List all reports as JSON:
.B maldet \-\-json\-report list
.TP
Quarantine all hits from a scan:
.B maldet \-q SCANID
.TP
Start real\-time inotify monitoring (foreground):
.B maldet \-m users
.TP
Start real\-time inotify monitoring (background daemon):
.B maldet \-b \-m users
.TP
Scan a file via the generic hook API:
.B hookscan.sh generic /path/to/file
.TP
Batch scan files from a list:
.B hookscan.sh generic \-\-list /tmp/filelist.txt
.TP
View hook scan activity (last 24 hours):
.B maldet \-\-report hooks
.TP
View hook scan activity filtered by mode:
.B maldet \-\-report hooks \-\-mode modsec
.TP
Fire an on\-demand digest alert:
.B maldet \-\-digest
.TP
Test email alerting with a synthetic scan report:
.B maldet \-\-test\-alert scan email
.TP
Test Slack digest delivery:
.B maldet \-\-test\-alert digest slack
